==Usage== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:9-->
# Select three points. The second point will be the apex of the angle. The geometry may be selected in the [[3D_View|3D View]] or in the drawing.
# If you have selected geometry in the 3D View: add the correct TechDraw View to the selection by selecting it in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]].
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* {{Version|1.0}}: If the {{MenuCommand|Dimensioning tools}} [[TechDraw_Preferences#Dimensions|preference]] is set to {{Value|Single tool}} (default): press the down arrow to the right of the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_Dimension.svg||x16px]][[Image:Toolbar_flyout_arrow.svg|x16px]]}} button and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:TechDraw_3PtAngleDimension.svg|16px]] Angle Dimension From 3 Points}} option from the dropdown.
#* If this preference has a different value (and in {{VersionMinus|0.21}}): press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_3PtAngleDimension.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_3PtAngleDimension|Angle Dimension From 3 Points]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Dimensions → [[Image:TechDraw_3PtAngleDimension.svg|16px]] Angle Dimension From 3 Points}} option from the menu.
# A dimension is added to the View.
# The dimension may be dragged to the desired position.
# If needed, add tolerances as described on [[TechDraw_Geometric_dimensioning_and_tolerancing#Tolerances|this page]].

